{
  "description": "Cross-language consistency fixture for KeyTermVerifier (issue #29). Each case builds a SessionState from `task_instruction`, runs KeyTermVerifier::verify against `summary` with the given `hints`, and asserts `passed` and `missing_items` (normalized, lowercased, first-occurrence order). Term extraction: lowercase the source, split on runs of [^a-z0-9], drop tokens shorter than 4 chars, dedupe preserving first-occurrence order. v1 limitation: only keep_current_task_state contributes source terms (from task_instruction); the other four hints add no terms. ASCII only.",
  "cases": [
    {
      "name": "full_pass_all_terms_present",
      "summary": "We will refactor the parser module to be faster.",
